TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$k = random(3,8,1);
$h = random(1,5,1);
$h2=2*$h;
$c= $h*$h+2*$k;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The parabola given by the equation \( 2y-$c=x^2+$h2 x \) has its vertex at \( (h,k) \) for:$BR
\( h= \)\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = -$h;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and$BR
\( k= \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =  $k;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

